			<div class="content" id="post-content-2278276">
									

<p>First, I am seriously indebted to Light for <a href="/the-flytrap">The Flytrap</a> and Bright for <a href="/ecceperago">Ecce Perago</a> and <a href="/annon">Annon</a>, without which this tale would not exist.</p>
<p>Thank you also to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Clef for an absolutely incredible amount of editing and improvements &#8212; just, holy shit. Clef did an unbelievable amount of work on this.</li>
<li>TroyL for a <em>ton</em> of concepts for the O5 Council, many of which I used here: in particular the concepts/characters for One &amp; Three [partially], Eight, Ten, Eleven, Twelve, Lament, and the final scene.</li>
<li>Light for practically writing Five's scene, concepts/characters for Five and Seven, and helping inspire the entire story.</li>
<li>DrMann for practically writing the first half of Four's scene, also Four's concept. Also a <em>lot</em> of improvement on One's scene, and much of One's concept/character.</li>
<li>Bright for the concepts/characters for One (partially), Three (partially), Six, the original Nine, and Thirteen. Plus inspiring Ten, Eleven, and Twelve, and helping inspire the entire story.</li>
<li>Photosynthetic for Nine's concept/character and scene.</li>
<li>Kestin for a lot of very helpful critique.</li>
<li>&#8230;and a ton of other people for a lot of very helpful critique.</li>
<li>&#8230;and a ton of other people whose concepts I <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">ripped off</span> homaged/referenced/used in this.</li>
</ul>
<p>Fun fact: each scene in this tale was originally two to five times longer, with most of the same content. Bright pointed out it was bloated, and Clef did the lion's share of the editing. &lt;3</p>
