<p>This&#8230; Was pretty disappointing.</p>
<p>I liked the characterizations of the O5 for the most part, but I got the sense that the whole point of this article was mounting tension going up to the vote.</p>
<p>Then the vote comes, and doesn't pass&#8230; Then 10 stands up for what I'm assuming was to be a passionate speech that turns the tide! Instead she rattles off a (frankly) unconvincing speech, and the powerful, wise council who I would have hoped put SOME thought behind their original votes basically says &quot;eh, ok&quot;. All this build up for that?</p>
<p>edit: was wrong about how long her speech was, but I still think it's bland and unconvincing. It doesn't address much of the concerns the naysayers made, from my reading.</p>

